The paper deals with the problem of learning mixture parameters of multivariate Gaussians, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning. The paper proposes an algorithm that has a polynomial running time and data requirement, which is a key topic in the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) to develop the algorithm. The paper's focus on clustering and density estimation suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
